<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="A" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Angel2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Angel,</orth> a gold coin worth ten shillings (described in <bibl n="shak. mv 2.7.56" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. II, 7, 56</bibl>: <emph>they have in England a coin that bears the figure of an angel stamped in gold</emph>): <bibl n="shak. wiv 2.2.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. II, 2, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. err 4.3.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Err. IV, 3, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 2.590" default="NO" valid="yes">John II, 590</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.3.8" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.2.6" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 2, 6</bibl>. Quibbles between the two significations: <bibl n="shak. wiv 1.3.60" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. I, 3, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.2.187" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 2, 187</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>